title: Polarization effects in the C-12(3He,pp) reaction at 33 MeV.

x4freetext: Polarization effects in the C-12(3He,pp) reaction
at 33 MeV.

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Birmingham, England, United Kingdom

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.460, p.529 (1986)

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Birmingham, England, United Kingdom

x4freetext: Self-supporting 10 mg/cm2 carbon target was used.
The reaction products were detected
in four delta E-E counter telescopes, each consisting
of a 100 mu-m surface-barrier detector and a 5 mm
Si(Li) detector. The data were taken in two different
arrangements of the telescopes inside the scattering
chamber.
33.3 MeV polarized He-3 beam

x4freetext: No information about source of uncertainty
SD: Corrections in Subents 012, 013.

x4freetext: Two telescopes were positioned symmetrically below and
above the horizontal plane, one pair to the left and
one to the right of the incident beam, keeping the
polar angle theta equal for all telescopes. Angle
definition: ANG is the polar angle between the He-2
cluster and He-3 beam direction. ANG-AZ is the angle
between the reaction planes.

x4freetext: Co-planar geometry was used. In this geometry all four
telescopes were situated in one plane perpendicular to
the spin symmetry axis. Angle definition: ANG-CM is
the polar angle between the He-2 cluster and He-3 beam
direction. ANG1 is the polar angle between the first
proton and He-3 beam direction. ANG2 is the polar
angle between the second proton and He-3 beam
direction. ANG-AZ is the angle between the reaction
planes.
